    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "```\n(17:58:46) antares79: pchote: I assume you mean it's a race condition? sth. in RenderBuilding overwrites the DefaultAnimation before the action has a chance to run?\n(18:05:20) pchote: antares79: yeah\n(18:36:57) antares79: pchote: ok, thanks. I thought that having game logic be run from the rendering parts was kinda nasty\n(18:38:46) pchote: antares79: for what its worth, I tried to trick penev into fixing this yesterday\n(18:40:27) pchote: I've been steering his upgradeable rendering stuff to cover an issue i've been planning / working on for a couple of years\n(18:40:46) pchote: which is to replace our Render* subclasses with the base RenderSprites plus With*\n(18:40:56) pchote: his WithBody being the next part of that\n(18:41:06) pchote: that now includes an open / start sequence\n(18:41:15) pchote: for buildings we can just set that to the make animation\n(18:41:23) pchote: possibly via a subclass, though\n(18:41:32) pchote: and then use upgrades to cover the logic half of it\n(18:41:38) pchote: which we already have an issue about\n(18:42:27) pchote: we could perhaps even do this without the integrated make animation if we wanted to use two different With* sequences\n(18:42:32) pchote: and have them switch based on the upgrade\n```\n"
